This paper is about event detection and classification using neural networks, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the performance of different neural network architectures, which suggests that it could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel GRU-based model that combines syntactic information and temporal structure, which could be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
